info.senderName: NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly (New Jersey, Delaware, Southeastern Pennsylvania)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 26 at 10:20AM EST by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor flooding caused by runoff from the recent heavy rainfall is expected. * WHERE...A portion of Somerset County, New Jersey. * WHEN...Until 400 PM EST. * IMPACTS...Minor river flooding is occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1020 AM EST, minor flooding was occurring around the confluence of the North Branch and the South Branch of the Raritan River. - Some locations that will experience minor flooding include... Branchburg Township, Bridgewater Township and Hillsborough Township. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas.
